I will never spend money on that part again, if I ever come back. I explained to the nice gentleman that took our order that I have never been here before. Those two rude ladies. I asked for fries when I ordered my sandwich, Also requested lettuce tomato and onion  on my Cuban and it was put on the hamburger. When I asked about the fries with my Italian sand. She said you were supposed to ask for fries when you order. I said I did. And in return, she turns to the other lady and says what is she talking about. The other lady responds I don’t know so they walk away. Really? I just spent $100 in y’all business. Did she think I was just trying to get free fries or something?  If tge gentleman didn’t hear me then charge me and make them, such disregard will have me spend my money somewhere else. Just a bit of advice; your business either prospers or go down the tubes depending upon whom you have as a spokesperson for your business. Whether it’s a rude cashier or cook. Amazing Cassata Cake!!! I called Thursday morning around 9-930am and spoke to a lovely woman named Kathy. I was looking for a cannoli pie for my sister but Kathy said they make a Cassata cake and although she wasn’t sure they had any made, she said she’d check and call me back in 15-30 minutes. I was happy that she called me back letting me know they would have one ready for me in the afternoon by 2pm. When I walked into the bakery, I was greeted by a staff member and while waiting for my cake to get a happy birthday ribbon, a few staff members asked if I needed any help (I was roaming around the bakery looking at all the delicious looking pastries!). The staff was very friendly and I have no complaints! Reading some of these other reviews made me sad that people are so judgmental. It’s very obvious to this Italian that the Alessi family takes great pride in their business. Thank you for the yummy cake!! We will be back!

Drove from punta Gorda for a day trip in Tampa was hoping to try a good bakery while there alessi got good reviews so decided to stop in they had a large selection they were pricy but i was willing to pay because it's not every day you get fresh baked Italian cookies i spent $50 in cookies and brought them home and invited the whole family We all agreed not Italian at all and not even good cookies (that last part is personal preference) But definitely not authentic It is like someone went to Publix and bought the Italian cookie sampler and try to recreate them these are not Italian bakery recipes They were very bland and dry and not buttery and flavorful like true Italian cookies If you come here expecting authentic Italian cookies expect to leave disappointed and broke If it wasn't so far I would go back the next day for a refund I always like to end on a happy note though I cannot say everything I tried was bad the almond horn while not authentic was very very good! And the guava pastry was also delicious! They are doing some good things and the food also looked good too but as for the Italian cookies I was highly disappointed especially at the price I paid All in all alessi has some good things I don't want to say the place is terrible at all but the Italian cookies really need some work if you're expecting authentic Italian cookies I would pass but if you're looking for a unique bakery with a large selection this is the place you are looking for

This is a childhood bakery that love to come to a least once a week. Now living in Texas, I really miss this place but on my last visit, I can really see they need some more improvements.  Service: All employees were very nice and greeted me as I came into the door. They provided me with great smiles and willing answer any questions I might have had. With the minor rush, they were able to get through the rush actual quickly.  Food: The food is the one thing that will bring you in every time. With my current visit, I had Cuban sandwich and devil crab. They both were delicious and while waiting, I was able sample some of their great pastries. This is one thing that I never forget as a child that always brought me back. They had some of your old favorites and some new selections as well.  Overall: The only reason I am giving them 3 stars because the overall improvements of the store. This bakery has been around for years and I feel they have not taken the pride in remolding the store and providing needed improvements with keeping the tradition of the store. I’ve noticed they remodel since being a child, but I know this store (company) could do better.  I will continue to enjoy their food and being part of Tampa’s great tradition, but I hope changes will be made soon.

It honestly hurts my heart to write this review. When my husband and I were newly married and lived in here Tampa we used to go there on a weekly basis. Now, 20 years later, we are  ack in Florida for vacation and decided to share it with our kids. The food is still incredible, but the service was sorely lacking. We got there at 5:30 two times this week and tried to order from the grill. The lady reluctantly cooked our food both times but told us that they close at 6pm and that she wasn't supposed to still be running grill orders and she told us they were out of everything from being busy. Both times. Then, a girl at the bakery counter was frustrated that people kept coming in because "it's Friday and we are ready to go home but people KEEP coming in for cookies." Her nametag said she was in training so she may just not know how things are done and I'm sure it was a rough day, but the Alessi's that I remember had a joy and friendliness about it that I was hoping to share with my kids. I will definitely be back for the food, and with lower expectations.  There were two people there that were awesome. A guy who was super fast at filling bakery orders, and a super friendly girl that helped in areas all over but I didn't catch her name. Hopefully they can train the others.  ***edited to add...my daughter is now throwing up from the Cuban mini sliders that had been in the cooler for a couple of days.
Our wedding cake was stunning and tasted delightful. Thank you for making our day that much more special.

Cake was amazing. I went to Publix and they gave me every excuse in the world as to why they couldn't promise me a cake that looked exactly as i described.  Alessi's came through big time. They simply said yes, we can do that, the decorator even said i will make it look even better. And oh boy did she! Just look at the pictures, incredible cake with great details without it being over the top or too busy.  Publix is a joke, so spend the extra small amount of money and go to Alessi's , they will give you what you ask for, very good work!  GREAT JOB!!! 10/10!!!!

I did a little Tampa staycation this week with some friends from out of town. We were staying in a hotel down the street from Alessi and I took them here for breakfast the first morning. Over in the sweets, the girls are pleasant as can be, and the goodies are amazing. I recommend the creme brulee bread pudding, the apple cake, and the cream horns.  Follow them on FB for their weekly BOGO specials, and go get your fat on!

For $2.75, it is fairly priced as it is a bit smaller than the average cupcake. The lemon bar had a nice after tang to it. Definitely different than your average lemon bar. Loved the strawberry cake. It wasn't too sweet and reminded me of Asian pastry.

Odd gripe: the entire time eating there, there's an audio clip that is played over the whole building speakers thanking you for visiting the restaurant. Every time we'd be in the middle of a conversation, we'd have to stop talking until the droning audio clip would finish. This occurred seemingly every 10-15 minutes.  Edit since i cannot reply:  Sorry for the loss, however every 10 minutes is a bit much, and the volume is way high. I get that you want to thank your customers for visiting your shop, but it's the kind of thing that makes me not want to spend time there or money. Quickly went from "hey this is great, it's close to the office and I should visit more often" to "yeah nevermind, I can't even enjoy being here, we'll go somewhere else."

I made the mistake of choosing Alessi for my wedding cake. The service was good when I was tasting, selecting and ordering my cake, but it all went downhill on my wedding day. The top of my cake was lopsided on delivery. We were told there was nothing they could do without spoiling the looks further trying to fix it. Then the top fell off midway through the reception. Luckily, there were people nearby who saw it sliding off and caught it and sort of shoved it back up. My wedding photos have a lopsided, tilting cake in it. After I returned from my honeymoon, I called them and told them of the fiasco. They offered a partial refund ($300) once I dropped off the cake fountain. I dropped it off, but no one was at the bakery, so I asked if I could drop it off at the deli counter. I was told yes, and I did so. I put my name and contact information on a piece of paper on the inside of the bag containing the fountain. When I still had not received my refund of $300 plus the $25 deposit on the fountain after a couple of weeks, I called them. They said they never received the fountain and that would issue a check after they received it. I told them I had dropped it off at the deli counter and described the person who took it. They said they would check and call back. A week later, I still hadn't heard back so I called them. They said they checked, but never got the fountain and refused to send any money back. I finally said, just take the $25 out of the $300 you owe me. They said they would check into it. After waiting and waiting again, I called back and they said they didn't know what I was talking about regarding a refund. I finally gave up. I do NOT recommend this place due to honesty issues with their staff.

Came here and absolutely splurged on goodies, all of them amazing. They had bogo on the guava and cheese turnovers, Eclairs, and a few other goodies. When I came the guava and cheese turnovers had just come out fresh and thank goodness for BOGO because I couldn't stop at one. The first bite of that guava and cheese turnover was absolute heaven. Definitely the best thing I bought there. The pastry was light and crunchy, and the guava jam filling was delightfully sweet with the mild cheese flavor to balance it all out. I've had quite a bit of guava and cheese pastries by now and Alessi's is my favorite so far.  I also bought 4 of the cookies: a chocolate filled one, apricot jam filled, fig jam filled, and a traditional Italian wedding cookie. Favorite was the fig filled, but the rest of them were by no means bad.  I also got a mini eclair, mini cannoli, carrot cake pop, rainbow cookie, and a 9-inch carved Cuban. The Cuban was definitely delicious, not the best, but really good. Carrot cake pop was good, but the chocolate/frosting the cake was dipped in was a bit too thick and sweet for my tastes. The mini eclair and cannoli were both great- but if I came back, I would definitely get the cannoli again. The rainbow cookie was my least favorite from everything I bought, but it was still very tasty and I don't regret giving it a taste.  Overall, a great time and would definitely like to come again!

Went to pick up some goodies for my birthday tomorrow and some lunch for today. Not one person greeted me when I walked in. When I got in line to order a sandwich, there was a little line. As I stood there for quite sometime for my turn to order, it looks as if the have a super slow process in completing orders. You place your order, and then the 3 girls make it, sell it and then take the next order. After finally ordering,the girl informed me that they will bring the order to me if I leave my number on the table since I was staying to eat there.  I went to the bakery side to get a few things. Yet again, not one person greeted me or informed me they would be with me in a moment. Out of the 6 girls behind the counter, only one person was actually attending to guests. 3 of the girls were having a personal conversation in the corner. One of them was actually crying, right in full view of the customers. After waiting 15 minutes, the one woman actually working finally addressed me. I was able to order my bakery items and while I was waiting for her to box them, the deli employee came over to give me my sandwich. I was completely floored how bad their customer service is. They completely ignore the customers coming in. I was there about 11:30 am so not sure why we were ignored. There was another woman who came in and was standing next to me who waited even longer for anyone to help her. Great food, great bakery items but not worth the wait or the ignorance of the staff. Focus on customer service!!!!! Customers should be greeted immediately even if you can’t help them right away. At least greet them and let them you know will be with them shortly. That gives us the understanding you know we are standing their to give you business. Sad to see how downhill it has gone over the years!!!!

I bought 5 kinds of dessert. Staff are super friendly and attentive. They have a wide array of desserts. I only gave 3 stars because the foods and dessert, appear and taste just simple and basic, lacking innovation. They have great prices though. Their "hello dolly" was extremely sweet. The toffee brownies a little bit dry. The "wedding cookies" tasted like bland powder. Also not fond of the italian cookies. For variety, price, and service, 5 stars. I prioritize quality taste more so I gave only 3 stars.

A dream for all sweet tooth people. The cakes were really delicious and not so over sugary. We used to come here quite often to get some birthday cake for the birthday parties. Even small treats like cookies or scones were also tasty and scrumptious. My most favorite cake here was cheesecake of all kinds, not to mention tiramisu and the Black Forest.

I was with friends from  work.  I wanted them to taste a good pressed Cuban sandwich and decide if this was better than Simply Delicious in St. Petersburg.  Only one of them was disappointed in his choice of a fresh burger as it wasn't what he was accustomed to getting. So 4 out of five agreed with me as to the quality and seasoning for their lunch meal. I have grown up with the taste of Alessi's baked goods and lunch meals. As for the one thaet was disappointed I will take him back there and have him try a Philly cheese steak for a better result.

Food is generally good, both bakery and food items. Today however, I stopped in to get a few bakery items around 330. She was putting items on the counter right in front of me and didn't have any concept of personal space either. Also the floor was sticky. Annoying visit.

Love their Cuban sandwiches, and their wedding cake is awe inspiring. They made our original and have twice recreated the top tier for a very low fee. Love this place.
